        "collapsible-tab-1": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Size Guide",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "{% comment %}\n  LOGIC:\n  Checks Shopify Standard Taxonomy (product.category.name).\n  FIXED: 'Earring' check is moved to the TOP. \n  This prevents earrings from accidentally triggering the 'Ring' guide.\n{% endcomment %}\n\n{%- assign category_name = product.category.name | downcase -%}\n\n{%- if category_name contains 'earring' or category_name contains 'stud' or category_name contains 'hoop' -%}\n\n  <div class=\"earring-size-guide\">\n    <p>Whether you are looking for a subtle stud or a statement hoop, understanding the scale is key. Use these tips to visualize how a <strong>Griffin and Co</strong> piece will sit on your ear:</p>\n    \n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>For Hoops & Huggies:</strong> The most important measurement is the <em>Inner Diameter</em>. Measure the distance from your piercing hole to the edge of your earlobe. Your hoop's inner diameter must be larger than this measurement to fit comfortably.</li>\n      <li><strong>For Studs & Drops:</strong> Hold a ruler against your ear to visualize the size (mm). A 3mm stud is very subtle, while a 7mm stud covers most of the lobe.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p><strong>Expert Tips:</strong> For a hoop to \"hug\" the ear tightly, measure the distance from your piercing to the bottom of your lobe and add 1-2mm for clearance. If your piercing is higher up on the lobe, you will need a larger diameter.</p>\n    <br>\n    <hr>\n    <br>\n\n    <h5>Earring Size & Style Reference Chart</h5>\n    <table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; table-layout: fixed; text-align: left;\">\n      <thead>\n        <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;\">\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Style Type</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Common Size (mm)</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Visual Description</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Best For</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Tiny Stud</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">3mm - 4mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Very subtle sparkle</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Second/Third piercings</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Standard Stud</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">5mm - 7mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Covers lower lobe</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Everyday Main Lobe</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Huggie Hoop</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">6mm - 9mm (ID)</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Hugs the ear tight</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Cartilage or Small Lobes</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Small Hoop</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">10mm - 14mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Sits just under lobe</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Minimalist Everyday</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Medium Hoop</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">15mm - 25mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Noticeable \"Gap\"</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Classic Day-to-Night</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Statement Hoop</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">30mm - 50mm+</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Jawline length</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Evening / Statement</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">\n      <h6>Need Bespoke Assistance?</h6>\n      <p>Our expert jewellers can advise on fit for non-standard piercings or cartilage placements. <a href=\"https://griffinfinejewellery.com/pages/contact\" title=\"Contact Us\"><strong>Contact Griffin and Co today.</strong></a></p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #eee; background-color: #fafafa; border-radius: 4px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin: 0;\">\n        <strong>Looking for more detail?</strong> \n        Read our <a href=\"/blogs/guide-jewellery-sizing-guide/\" title=\"Jewellery Sizing Guide\"><strong>Jewellery Sizing Blog</strong></a> for a deep dive into measuring tips, international conversions, and secret gifting advice.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  {%- elsif category_name contains 'ring' -%}\n  \n  <div class=\"ring-size-guide\">\n    <p>Ensure a perfect fit for your <strong>ring</strong> by using one of the methods below:</p>\n    \n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Measure an Existing Ring:</strong> Measure the <em>inside diameter</em> (mm) of a ring that fits the same finger perfectly.</li>\n      <li><strong>Measure Your Finger:</strong> Wrap string or paper around the base of your finger. Mark the overlap and measure the length (circumference) against a ruler.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p><strong>Expert Tips:</strong> Measure at the end of the day when fingers are warmest. If your knuckle is significantly larger than the base of your finger, size up.</p>\n    <br>\n    <hr>\n    <br>\n\n    <h5>Full A-Z Ring Size Conversion Chart</h5>\n    <table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left;\">\n      <thead>\n        <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;\">\n          <th style=\"width: 25%;\">UK Size</th>\n          <th style=\"width: 25%;\">US Size</th>\n          <th style=\"width: 25%;\">EU Size</th>\n          <th style=\"width: 25%;\">Inside Diameter (mm)</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">A</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">0.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">37.8</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">12.04</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">B</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">1</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">39.1</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">12.45</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">C</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">1.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">40.4</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">12.85</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">D</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">2</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">41.7</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">13.26</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">E</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">2.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">42.9</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">13.67</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">F</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">3</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">44.2</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">14.07</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">G</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">3.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">45.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">14.48</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">H</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">4</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">46.8</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">14.88</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">I</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">4.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">48.0</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">15.29</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">J</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">49.3</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">15.70</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">K</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">5.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">50.6</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">16.10</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">L</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">6</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">51.9</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">16.51</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">M</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">6.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">53.1</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">16.92</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">N</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">7</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">54.4</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">17.32</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">O</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">7.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">55.7</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">17.73</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">P</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">8</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">57.0</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">18.14</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Q</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">8.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">58.3</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">18.54</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">R</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">9</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">59.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">18.95</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">S</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">9.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">60.8</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">19.35</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">T</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">10</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">62.1</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">19.76</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">U</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">10.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">63.4</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">20.17</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">V</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">11</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">64.6</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">20.57</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">W</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">11.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">65.9</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">20.98</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">X</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">12</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">67.2</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">21.39</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Y</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">12.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">68.5</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">21.79</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Z</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">13</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">69.7</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">22.20</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">\n      <h6>Need Bespoke Assistance?</h6>\n      <p>Our expert jewellers can help you find a size not listed or help you measure discreetly for a gift. <a href=\"https://griffinfinejewellery.com/pages/contact\" title=\"Contact Us\"><strong>Contact Griffin and Co today.</strong></a></p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #eee; background-color: #fafafa; border-radius: 4px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin: 0;\">\n        <strong>Looking for more detail?</strong> \n        Read our <a href=\"/blogs/guide-jewellery-sizing-guide/\" title=\"Jewellery Sizing Guide\"><strong>Jewellery Sizing Blog</strong></a> for a deep dive into measuring tips, international conversions, and secret gifting advice.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  {%- elsif category_name contains 'bracelet' or category_name contains 'bangle' or category_name contains 'anklet' -%}\n\n  <div class=\"bracelet-size-guide\">\n    <p>Ensure a perfect fit for your <strong>Griffin and Co</strong> piece by using one of the methods below:</p>\n    \n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>For Bracelets & Anklets:</strong> Wrap a flexible tape measure or string around your wrist or ankle bone. Mark the overlap and measure the length against a ruler to find your <em>circumference</em>.</li>\n      <li><strong>For Bangles:</strong> Close your hand (tucking your thumb toward your pinky). Measure the circumference around the widest part of your hand—usually the knuckles—to ensure the bangle can slide on.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p><strong>Expert Tips:</strong> For a standard \"comfort fit,\" add 1.5cm to 2cm to your wrist measurement. For bangles, the measurement of your closed hand is the <em>minimum</em> size you should select.</p>\n    <br>\n    <hr>\n    <br>\n\n    <h5>Bracelet & Bangle Size Conversion Chart</h5>\n    <table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; table-layout: fixed; text-align: left;\">\n      <thead>\n        <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;\">\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Size Category</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Circumference (cm)</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Bangle Diameter (mm)</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Recommended For</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Extra Small</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">15 - 16 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">55 mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Petite Wrists</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Small</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">16 - 17 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">60 mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Women's Standard</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Medium</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">18 - 19 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">65 mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Men's Small / Loose Fit</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Large</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">19 - 20 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">70 mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Men's Standard / Anklet</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Extra Large</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">21 - 22 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">75 mm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Men's Large / Anklet</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">\n      <h6>Need Bespoke Assistance?</h6>\n      <p>Our expert jewellers can create custom lengths or help you choose the right size for a gift. <a href=\"https://griffinfinejewellery.com/pages/contact\" title=\"Contact Us\"><strong>Contact Griffin and Co today.</strong></a></p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #eee; background-color: #fafafa; border-radius: 4px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin: 0;\">\n        <strong>Looking for more detail?</strong> \n        Read our <a href=\"/blogs/guide-jewellery-sizing-guide/\" title=\"Jewellery Sizing Guide\"><strong>Jewellery Sizing Blog</strong></a> for a deep dive into measuring tips, international conversions, and secret gifting advice.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  {%- elsif category_name contains 'necklace' or category_name contains 'pendant' or category_name contains 'chain' -%}\n\n  <div class=\"necklace-size-guide\">\n    <p>Finding the perfect drop for your pendant or necklace ensures it complements your neckline and style. Use these methods to find your ideal length:</p>\n    \n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Measure an Existing Chain:</strong> Lay a chain you love flat on a table and measure its length in inches or cm (including the clasp).</li>\n      <li><strong>The String Test:</strong> Cut a piece of string to a specific length (e.g., 18 inches). Place it around your neck to see exactly where it will sit. This is crucial if you are layering chains.</li>\n    </ul>\n\n    <p><strong>Expert Tips:</strong> The most common length for women is <strong>18 inches (45cm)</strong>. If buying for a heavy pendant, remember the weight will pull the chain into a \"V\" shape, making it sit slightly lower than a plain chain.</p>\n    <br>\n    <hr>\n    <br>\n\n    <h5>Standard Necklace Length Guide</h5>\n    <table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; table-layout: fixed; text-align: left;\">\n      <thead>\n        <tr style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;\">\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Length (Inch)</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Length (cm)</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Style Name</th>\n          <th style=\"padding: 8px; width: 25%;\">Where it Sits</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">14\" - 16\"</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">35 - 40 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Choker</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Base of the neck</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">18\"</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">45 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Princess</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Collarbone (Standard)</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">20\" - 24\"</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">50 - 60 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Matinee</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Between collarbone & bust</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">30\" - 36\"</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">76 - 90 cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Opera</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Below the bust</td></tr>\n        <tr><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">36\"+</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">90+ cm</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Rope</td><td style=\"padding: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;\">Waist (often doubled)</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">\n      <h6>Need Bespoke Assistance?</h6>\n      <p>Our expert jewellers can help you find a custom chain length or advise on layering styles. <a href=\"https://griffinfinejewellery.com/pages/contact\" title=\"Contact Us\"><strong>Contact Griffin and Co today.</strong></a></p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #eee; background-color: #fafafa; border-radius: 4px;\">\n      <p style=\"margin: 0;\">\n        <strong>Looking for more detail?</strong> \n        Read our <a href=\"/blogs/guide-jewellery-sizing-guide/\" title=\"Jewellery Sizing Guide\"><strong>Jewellery Sizing Blog</strong></a> for a deep dive into measuring tips, international conversions, and secret gifting advice.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  {%- endif -%}",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
